egi n  {aligned}  &  \bm {Q} = \bm {K} = \bm {Z}_i + \bm {E}_{f},\\ & \bm {V} = \bm {Z}_i, \\ &\hat {\bm {Z}}_i = Att_{dec.}(\bm {Q},\bm {K},\bm {V}). \end {aligned} \label {eq:multiheawd} 
(6)
Regarding the first line in Eq. 6, same encoding is added
to the relation representations in the same frame as queries
and keys. The output from the last decoder layer is adopted
for final prediction. Because of the sliding widow, the rela-
tionships in a frame have various representation in different
batches. In this work, we choose the earliest representation
appearing in the windows.
